# üéØ Senior Developer Rules for Flutter Project
# These rules enforce professional code standards across the entire project

## üèóÔ∏è ARCHITECTURE & STRUCTURE

### Widget Design Patterns
- Always use `final class` for StatelessWidget/StatefulWidget for better performance
- Separate complex widgets into smaller, focused widget classes
- Use descriptive class names with underscore prefix for private widgets (e.g., `_DialogTitle`)
- Each widget should have a single responsibility
- Add descriptive documentation comments for all widget classes

### File Organization
- Use `part of` for widget files that belong to a main view
- Group related widgets in the same file when they're only used together
- Keep imports organized and remove unused imports

## üîß CONST USAGE RULES

### Mandatory Const Usage
- ALL StatelessWidget constructors MUST be const with `super.key`
- ALL static widgets MUST use `const` keyword
- ALL static values (padding, margins, colors, sizes) MUST be const
- Use `const` for BorderRadius, EdgeInsets, Colors, and other immutable objects

### Examples:
```dart
// ‚úÖ CORRECT
final class _MyWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  const _MyWidget({super.key});
  
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return const Column(
      children: [
        Icon(AppIcons.home, size: AppIconSizes.medium),
        SizedBox(height: AppIconSizes.small),
      ],
    );
  }
}

// ‚ùå WRONG
class MyWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  MyWidget();
  
  Widget build(context) {
    return Column(
      children: [
        Icon(Icons.home, size: 24),
        SizedBox(height: 8),
      ],
    );
  }
}
```

## üìä MAGIC NUMBERS ELIMINATION

### No Magic Numbers Policy
- Replace ALL magic numbers with named constants
- Use static const variables for any numeric value
- Group related constants in dedicated classes

### Examples:
```dart
// ‚úÖ CORRECT
final class _MyWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  const _MyWidget({super.key});
  
  static const double _containerHeight = 150;
  static const double _borderWidth = 2;
  static const double _opacity = 0.1;
  
  // ... use _containerHeight, _borderWidth, _opacity
}

// ‚ùå WRONG
Container(
  height: 150,
  decoration: BoxDecoration(
    border: Border.all(width: 2),
    color: Colors.blue.withOpacity(0.1),
  ),
)
```

## üé® UTILITY CONSTANTS USAGE

### Mandatory Utility Classes
- **Icons**: ALWAYS use `AppIcons.iconName` instead of `Icons.iconName`
- **Sizes**: ALWAYS use `AppIconSizes.size` instead of numeric values
- **Colors**: ALWAYS use `ColorsCustom.colorName` instead of `Colors.colorName`
- **Padding**: ALWAYS use `PagePadding.paddingType()` instead of `EdgeInsets`
- **BorderRadius**: ALWAYS use `CustomRadius.size` instead of `BorderRadius.circular()`

### Required Imports:
```dart
import 'package:lifeclient/product/utility/constants/app_icons.dart';
import 'package:lifeclient/product/utility/constants/app_icon_sizes.dart';
import 'package:lifeclient/product/utility/decorations/colors_custom.dart';
import 'package:lifeclient/product/utility/decorations/custom_radius.dart';
import 'package:life_shared/life_shared.dart'; // for PagePadding
```

### Examples:
```dart
// ‚úÖ CORRECT
Icon(
  AppIcons.home,
  size: AppIconSizes.medium,
  color: ColorsCustom.brandeisBlue,
)

Container(
  padding: const PagePadding.generalAllLow(),
  decoration: const BoxDecoration(
    borderRadius: CustomRadius.medium,
    color: ColorsCustom.gray,
  ),
)

// ‚ùå WRONG
Icon(
  Icons.home,
  size: 24,
  color: Colors.blue,
)

Container(
  padding: EdgeInsets.all(12),
  decoration: BoxDecoration(
    borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(12),
    color: Colors.grey[200],
  ),
)
```

## üåç LOCALIZATION RULES

### Mandatory LocaleKeys Usage
- NEVER use hardcoded strings in UI
- ALWAYS use `LocaleKeys.key.tr()` for all user-facing text
- Import: `import 'package:lifeclient/product/init/language/locale_keys.g.dart';`

### Examples:
```dart
// ‚úÖ CORRECT
Text(LocaleKeys.button_save.tr())
AppBar(title: Text(LocaleKeys.settings_title.tr()))

// ‚ùå WRONG
Text('Save')
AppBar(title: Text('Settings'))
```

## ‚ö° PERFORMANCE RULES

### Widget Optimization
- Use `final class` for all custom widgets
- Prefer `const` constructors everywhere possible
- Use `const` for static widget trees
- Avoid rebuilding widgets unnecessarily

### Memory Management
- Use proper widget lifecycle methods
- Dispose controllers and streams properly
- Avoid memory leaks in StatefulWidgets

## üé® STYLING RULES

### Theme Integration
- Use `context.general.textTheme` for text styles
- Follow the established design system
- Maintain consistent spacing and sizing

### Color and Design
- Use semantic color names from ColorsCustom
- Follow established padding patterns from PagePadding
- Use consistent border radius from CustomRadius

## üìù CODE QUALITY RULES

### Documentation
- Add clear comments for complex logic
- Use descriptive variable and method names
- Document public APIs and widgets

### Error Handling
- Handle errors gracefully
- Provide user-friendly error messages
- Use proper exception handling

